article.headline: Bradley 78, North Dakota 69
article.story: PEORIA, Ill. -- Taylor Brown had 26 points and a career-high 14 rebounds Saturday night as Bradley remained unbeaten with a 78-69 victory over North Dakota. Walt Lemon Jr. added 19 points, and Jordan Prosser had 15 points and nine rebounds for the Braves, who are off to a 3-0 start for the first time since 2002. Troy Huff had 22 points and 12 rebounds for North Dakota (2-1). Patrick Mitchell added 15 points, and Aaron Anderson had 13. The first half featured five ties and seven lead changes until Bradley closed the period on an 11-2 run to go on top 34-25. North Dakota rallied and twice took one-point leads midway through the second half, but a 14-5 run by the Braves gave them a 69-59 lead with 2:07 left on Jake Eastman's jumper. Bradley is now 12-0 all-time against the Fighting Sioux, although the teams hadn't met since January of 1969.
